rooms.Name: The Studio
rooms.Description:
This is Sargon's favorite place, his space at the craft center.  Two large
tables define the north and south boundries.  On these tables are several
clay vessels in various stages of completion.  The concrete wall to the east
is covered with posters.  Against the wall is a desk full of clay tools and
ceramics books.  Next to the desk is a large garbage can of aging clay and
several recycle buckets.  The western border is a heavy shelving unit full
of completed ceramic wares.  In the center of the floor is a crappy Shimpo
throwing wheel.

rooms.Name: Opening Credits
rooms.Description: Along time ago, in a galaxy far, far away...

rooms.Name: In Space - Outside the Hanger Bay - Exploding into a Thousand Bits.
rooms.Description:
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

  "The Hitchhikers Guide to the Galaxy says that if you can hold a lungful
       of air you can survive the total vacuum of space. However, it does
       go on to say that with space being the mind boggling size that it is
       your chances of being picked up in that thirty seconds are 2 to the 
       power of 267709 to 1 against."

   Congratulations on Finding One of the "Top 3 most obvious Dt's" on 
     mud.

Please stop by again!!!!!

rooms.Name: Entrance Ramp of the Millenium Falcon
rooms.Description:
You have just stepped onto the ramp leading into the Millenium Falcon.  At 
the top you see a scruffy looking man waiting for nothing in particular.  The
Falcon looks prepped and ready to leave for some exotic location.  You hurry
up the ramp to talk to the man who is the only one that will let you in.  
Hope you brought your wallet because it's going to cost you to ride.

rooms.Name: Tie Pilot's Rec Room
rooms.Description:
This is where all the Tie Fighter pilots come after a long day shooting
Rebel star-fighters out of the sky.  It's quite cozy.  Posters all over
the wall and carpeting with nice soft beds.  The Empire likes to treat
it's pilots well, mainly because the first mission is usually a rookies
last.

Exits.Description: To the east, the Hangar Bay continues.

rooms.Name: Death Star Hangar Bay 1824
rooms.Description:
This is the secondary hanger bay, actually one of the many secondary bays.
The hanger is as large as the one you entered in the Falcon.  The ships 
outside the bay are buzzing around coming and going from here never allowing
the grass to grow beneath the pilot's feet.  You feel sorry for the many
pilots leaving from this bay.  Most won't return.  Oh well at least it's 
not you.

Exits.Description: To the south, you can see the Hangar Bay's Landing Zone.
To the west, the Hangar Bay continues.

rooms.Name: Garbage Compactor
rooms.Description:
The walls in this room are large and very slick.  The room is strewn with
garbage.  The stench is very bad.  You wish you had a gas mask to filter
this overpowering gas.  Of course the gas is not where the real danger lies
in this room.  As you entered the walls started closing in.  Fortunately
for you after crushing you the machine just stops.

rooms.Name: Service Tunnel
rooms.Description:
These tunnels allow service personel to fix whatever goes wrong on the 
Death Star if the lifts don't work.  They all look the same to you, but
the service personel must be able to tell the difference.  The tunnel
is all grey and very cold.  Fortunately it's safe.  And that's all that 
matters to you right now.

rooms.Name: Service Tunnel
rooms.Description:

Death Star if the lifts don't work.  They all look the same to you, but
the service personel must be able to tell the difference.  The tunnel
is all grey and very cold.  Fortunately it's safe.  And that's all that 
matters to you right now.

rooms.Name: Starfighter Maintenance Shed
rooms.Description:
This small room is where the maintenance crews come for tools or spare parts.
You can't see anything really special about the room other then that it is
quite cluttered and some really neat looking space ship peices.

Exits.Description: To the east, you see the Hangar Bay's Landing Zone
To the northeast, the Hangar Bay continues.

rooms.Name: Death Star Hanger Bay 1823
rooms.Description:
From here all the arriving ships land.  Be they friend or foe it doesn't
matter.  The Millenium Falcon is sitting in this bay, an innocent victim
in an enemy territory.  The huge tractor beam projectors are also in this 
room ready to snare any ship without the proper clearance codes.
Fortunately there are no guards here so you can escape from the Falcon without
fear of capture.  Enjoy your stay on the Death Star, may it be your first of
many.

Exits.Description: To the north, the Hangar Bay continues.
To the East is outer space. Get a flight suit before you enter.
To the south, the Hangar Bay continues.
To the west, the Hangar Bay continues.

rooms.Name: Space
rooms.Description:
You can see stars all around you. The ones in space and the ones infront of
your eyes.  The oxygen deprevation is getting to you.  That and the 
pressure.  You could stay but there really is no reason to.  After all your
about to be dead.

Exits.Description: To the west, you can see the Hangar Bay's Landing Zone.

rooms.Name: Service Tunnel
rooms.Description:
Of all the places to go you had to pick here.  This is the chute that
runs to the compactor.  The piles of moving trash are wierd mutations
and nothing at all to worry about.  Unfortunately once you've passed you
can't go back.  Oh well it's a swell ride.

rooms.Name: Dimly Lit Corridor
rooms.Description:
Your encounter with the Emperor is over.  You feel relieved.  This room is
kept dark to try to get you to still feeling afraid.  Of course after meeting
the Emperor this room is just a walk in the park.

rooms.Name: Death Star Hangar Bay - Western Wall
rooms.Description:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Below you, the polished black floor echos your footsteps as you make your
way through the numerous Stormtrooper Squads assembled for the arrival of
the Emperor's private shuttle escort.  Various power cell chargers and
droid maintenance workers populate the area.

Exits.Description: To the north, the Hangar Bay continues.
To the east, the Hangar Bay continues.

rooms.Name: Death Star Hangar Bay - Main Platform
rooms.Description:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Below you, the polished black floor echos your footsteps as you make your

Exits.Description: To the north, the Hangar Bay continues.
To the east, the Hangar Bay continues.
To the west, the Hangar Bay continues.
To the northeast, you can see the Hangar Bay's Landing Zone.

rooms.Name: Unshielded Hanger Bay
rooms.Description:
This hangar is currently under repair. The magnetic shielding is faulty
and offers no protection from the harshness of space.  As you keep standing
here you can feel your blood start to burst.  You realize you had better
leave if you want to survive.

Exits.Description: To the north, you can see the Hangar Bay's Landing Zone.

rooms.Name: Turbo Lift
rooms.Description:
This high speed elevator platform is a much better impovement to the cable
and counterweight elevators of old.  It works on repulsor-lift technology.
The lift is extremely fast and can rise fifty floors in what seems like a 
heartbeat.  Hold on it's about to move.

rooms.Name: Detention Level Corridor
rooms.Description:
This corridor is short and dimly lit.  Suiting the detention level spirit.
The prisoners are brought in through this corridor and lead to either a
long jail stay with little or no chance of leaving, or a long and painful
death.  Enjoy your visit to this level.  You might be staying awhile.

rooms.Name: Detention Level Security Checkpoint
rooms.Description:
This security checkpoint is armed with your average security Laser cannon. 
The cannon is turning towards you so you better run.

rooms.Name: Detention Level Cell-block A
rooms.Description:
This is the last sight many inmates see before they are imprisoned.  Not a 
pretty sight.  The hall is short with what looks like red running lights
in it.  Not a great sight to see when you're about to be imprisoned.
Of course this isn't a cruise this is a prison, and most of the inmates
are either gone mentally or just plain gone.  Hopefully you don't become
one of them.

rooms.Name: Cell
rooms.Description:
This is quite a bare cell.  The only furniture in it is the bench for
prisoners to sleep on.  You are glad you aren't one of the poor
helpless prisoners.  This would be a horrible place to die.  Nothing
to look at or do.  No wonder many prisoners give the Empire the
information that the Empire wants to hear.

rooms.Name: Main Corridor
rooms.Description:
This is a long winding corridor through the Death Star.  The floors are clean
enough to eat off of, and you can see your smiling(or maybe fearful) face in
it.  The walls are nondescript mainly because this battle station is the size
of a small moon and finding pretty pictures for all of them would take a   
couple of years to do.  You look around and realize that one corridor is
identical to another save for the way it leads.  Hopefully you don't get lost.

rooms.Name: Security Checkpoint
rooms.Description:
The walls, floors, and ceiling in this room are polished, grey metal.  This
is a standard security checkpoint.  A Red security computer monitors the 
station.  You were scanned for intent and concealed weapons the moment you
stepped into the room.  Cameras are recording your every movement and the
defensive grid has been charged.

rooms.Name: Tractor Beam Control Room
rooms.Description:
This is where the tractor beam controls are.  The room is alive with flashing
lights and a powerful hum.  The hum is coming from just behind the wall.
The actual control for the tractor beam is several large levers on the wall.
You can look down over the edge of the ledge and see a huge chasm.  You
wish you could see the bottom.

rooms.Name: Radiation Shield Room
rooms.Description:
This is a very large room with a very large warning symbol in it.  
"The Reactor is guarded from intrusion, enter at your own risk". 
The room you are in is safe enough but do you really want to try your
luck in the next room.  A small part of you is saying go for it
while another is saying don't even think about it.  Of course you
need to get the key to enter.  To get the key you have to persuade
the Moff to let go of it.  Think you can do it?

rooms.Name: Inside the Reactor
rooms.Description:
This large room is the home of the reactor.  The room is big enough
to fit several small fighters in it.  The reactor itself dominates the
middle of the room.  It glows and pulses giving off an ominous light.
This room is big enough to hide a ship in it.  Wonder what else it may
hide?

rooms.Name: Grand Moff Tarkin's Office
rooms.Description:
This is the Moff's lavish office.  It has art from many an extinct
cultures.  The chairs and the couch are pure leather.  From here you can 
see outside to a limited degree.  The dark cieling and dark floor help
you to see the starry sky from a little window in the wall.  The Moff
usually hides in here from the many nagging questions of the lower
ranking officials.  If you want to stay onboard to fight the Dark Lord 
maybe you should hide in here also.

rooms.Name: War Room
rooms.Description:
This is where the strategy for destroying the Rebels and for keeping planets
loyal to the Empire takes place.  The Officers are always bickering about
whose territory to protect more.  This room is sometimes graced by the Moff
but usually the quarrels are not worth the Moff's time.
There is a long table with many chairs seated around it here.  The Moff
sits at the head of the table while the others sit on the sides.

rooms.Name: Observation Room
rooms.Description:
From here you can see what the super laser destroys.  It's almost a front
row seat.  Except for the poor souls on the planet who get a better view.
The viewport is very large to accommadate all the viewers.  It also 
provides you with an excellent view of space.  The rest of the room is
quite dull so as to not distract the viewers.

rooms.Name: Super Laser Control Room
rooms.Description:
This is where the real power of the Death Star is controlled.  These screens
analyze the makeup of a planet and then allow the controllers to blow up 
the planet.  This one laser is more powerful then half the entire fleet.  The
many computers display different planets and technical reports for the 
laser firing crew.  With the levers and dials in this room life as we know
it on some planets will cease to exhist.  Mainly because the planet will 
be gone.

rooms.Name: In the Super Laser Cannon
rooms.Description:
This is where the super laser originates.  This cannon can vaporize planets
with a single blast.  The cannon is just huge.  You can't see where the
laser exits the cannon from.  Hopefully you are not present when they fire t
this thing.  The blast would be quite deadly to a single person.

rooms.Name: Security Checkpoint
rooms.Description:
The walls, floors, and ceiling in this room are polished, grey metal.  This
is a standard security checkpoint.  A Red security computer monitors the 
station.  You were scanned for intent and concealed weapons the moment you
stepped into the room.  Cameras are recording your every movement and the
defensive grid has been charged.

rooms.Name: Secondary Security Checkpoint.
rooms.Description:
This check point has a similar setup to the room you just left.  The room is
grey and sterile, because NOTHING that comes in here without proper clearance
leaves this room alive.  Warning sirens blare, warning the station of your
attempted....
Sorry, you're dead.

rooms.Name: Royal Guard's Post
rooms.Description:
Here stands the Emperor's personnally trained bodyguards.  The two of them
alone are usually enough.  If not then the Emperor has two with him at all
times.  The room is rather small.  The only real space in here is for
the few visitors and for the guards.  The room is an off-white color with
the Death Stars usual grey floors.  This room is rather cramped.  Maybe
you won't have to fight in this tight space.

rooms.Name: Dimly Lit Corridor
rooms.Description:
This is a very dark hall.  The floor is hard to see in the low lighting.
This lighting adds to the mood of seeing the almighty Emperor Palpatine.
To the south you can barely see a small room.  And to the east is the 
throne room.  Do you dare go in?

rooms.Name: Emperor Palpatine's Throne Room
rooms.Description:
From this room the Emperor controls most of the galaxy.  He sits in a
high backed, swiveling chair.  This allows him to peer out the viewport
or look at his humble subjects.  You can feel immense power radiating
from this room.  The fact that the two openings to the north and south
lead straight to the reactor doesn't help.  Don't get to close or you
might fall in.

rooms.Name: Dignitary's Lodgings
rooms.Description:
This is where the dignitaries from around the Empire come to wait for
an audience with the Emperor.  The room is very plush.  The walls
are covered with paintings of faraway places.  The room is lined with
several very comfortable couches. Maybe you should rest here a bit
before you seek out the Emperor.

rooms.Name: Service Tunnel
rooms.Description:
These tunnels allow service personel to fix whatever goes wrong on the 
Death Star if the lifts don't work.  They all look the same to you, but
the service personel must be able to tell the difference.  The tunnel
is all grey and very cold.  Fortunately it's safe.  And that's all that 
matters to you right now.

rooms.Name: Stormtrooper Garrison - Locker Area
rooms.Description:
This is where all the Stormtroopers keep their belongings.
This room is a soothing grey compared to the cold grey of the hall.
Each locker has an identification number so that the Stormtroopers
know which locker is theirs.  None of these lockers are empty.
Unless something has happened to the owner.

rooms.Name: Stormtrooper Garrison - Kitchen Area
rooms.Description:
Here is where all the Stormtroopers prepare their meals.
Actually all they have to do is heat the pre-prepared meals.
The kitchen is white all the way down to the grey floors.  An
occasional food stain is on the wall, but that will soon be cleaned
up.

rooms.Name: Stormtrooper Garrison - Sleeping Quarters
rooms.Description:
Welcome to the bedroom of Stormtroopers.  All the beds look very
comfortable.  Nobody is sleeping in any of them thanks to the reports
of intruders being onboard the station.  This room is kept dark so that
the stormtroopers don't have to deal with the lights.  Hopefully they
don't come back while you are napping here.

rooms.Name: Stormtrooper Garrison
rooms.Description:
This is where the Stormtroopers live.  They are treated very well.
This room appears to be a living room.  There are tables and chairs
and a couch scattered around.  The room is a nice soothing tan.  It
conveys peace to the stormtroopers who get to go out and blow stuff
up.

rooms.Name: Armory
rooms.Description:
This is the Stormtrooper's Armory.  All of there weapons are kept here
when not in use.  The room is bathed in a bright white light.  With
the white walls in here the light is reflected around leaving no nook
without at least a splash of light.  The weapons in here are arranged
nicely in long rows all the around the room.  The armor is also stored
in here.

rooms.Name: Access Ramp
rooms.Description:
This is the entrance to the Modified Corvette Mescue.  It is one of the
best corvettes in the fleet.  This ship was designed as a blockade
runner and has served that purpose time and again.  You look around and
see the hydrolics that work the hatch.  Occasionally a jet of steam will
shoot out of the coolant outlets.

rooms.Name: Main Hall of Corvette Mescue
rooms.Description:
The hall you are in as well as the others in this corvette are all white,
save for the grey steel floor.  The hall lacks pizazz.  It just is a hall.
You wonder as you stare out ahead of you, how could anybody stand to work
in these conditions day in and day out.  Then you realize your job is 
life or death and the people on this corvette have it easy.  You stare at
these walls that remind you of the life you lead and think, "I hate these
walls".

rooms.Name: Hall of the Corvette Mescue
rooms.Description:
The hall you are in as well as the others in this corvette are all white,
save for the grey steel floor.  The hall lacks pizazz.  It just is a hall.
You wonder as you stare out ahead of you, how could anybody stand to work
in these conditions day in and day out.  Then you realize your job is 
life or death and the people on this corvette have it easy.  You stare at
these walls that remind you of the life you lead and think, "I hate these
walls".

rooms.Name: Engine Room
rooms.Description:
This is the maintenance area for the engine system of the corvette.  You can
hear the roar of the engines through the bulkhead.  The engine room is bare
with no real need for any decorations.  The white walls and the grey of the
floor are shiny enough to see your face in.  The engine compartment itself 
is off limits.  The noise alone would deafen you without earprotection.
Fortunately for you the room is sealed shut.

rooms.Name: Bottom Gun Turret
rooms.Description:
This is the other major gun emplacement.  The view is quite similar to the
top view.  All of space can be seen, save for the part blocked by the ships
own hull.  This gun has seen better days.  The fireing mechanism seems to
be broken.  Maybe that is why the corvette is orbiting the Death Star.

rooms.Name: Top Gun Turret
rooms.Description:
This is one of the main gun emplacements on the ship.  It gives a great view
of space.  This is needed of course.  This is where the gunners shoot down
enemy craft.  From here you can see the Death Star and several battle scars
on the top of the craft.  Almost everywhere you look are Tie squadrons 
patrolling for incoming enemy craft.  Hopefully this turret won't come into
use while you are here.

rooms.Name: Hall of the Corvette Mescue
rooms.Description:
The hall you are in as well as the others in this corvette are all white,
save for the grey steel floor.  The hall lacks pizazz.  It just is a hall.
You wonder as you stare out ahead of you, how could anybody stand to work
in these conditions day in and day out.  Then you realize your job is 
life or death and the people on this corvette have it easy.  You stare at
these walls that remind you of the life you lead and think, "I hate these
walls".

rooms.Name: Bridge
rooms.Description:
This is where all the command decesions are made on the corvette Mescue.
Captain Rhein makes all the decisions here.  You can see many terminals
ablaze with activity.  The crewman are very busy.  The Emperor wants
security tight around here and these men are just the ones to do it.
The viewport shows the Death Star in all it's glory.  This corvette is
just waiting to take the Emperor back to Coruscant after he finishes
approving the construction.

rooms.Name: Central Chasm
rooms.Description:
That wasn't too smart, jumping over the railing like that.  You are sailing
through the central chasm of the battle station on a direct course to the
reactor.  The walls are made of smooth metal so there is nothing you can grab
to stop your fall.  Gravity is your captain and we hope you enjoy your flight.

rooms.Name: Beginning of the Movie
rooms.Description:
...

Little does Luke know that the GALACITC EMPIRE has secretly begun
construction on a new armored space station even more powerful than the
first dreaded Death Star.

When completed, this ultimate weapon will spell certain doom for the
small band of rebels struggling to restore freedom to the galaxy...

rooms.Name: Pain Chamber
rooms.Description:
Pain... Yep, that's what you are feeling right now.  This room is all that
is left of the alternate universe brought on by the ion storm.  Dr. F. still
uses this room to torture TV's Frank.
DEEP HURTING... DEEEEEEEEEP HUUUUURTING...

rooms.Name: Elevator to the Surface
rooms.Description:
You are now 13 floors below the surface.  The walls were roughly hewn
into the rock.  Is the green lighting coming from the photoelectric mosses
growing on the ceiling, or just the cheap studio lights.  Up leads to
safety and the other exit leads to insanity.

rooms.Name: Inside the Millenium Falcon
rooms.Description:
You are standing in the center of the crew quarters.  One wall is occupied 
by the navi-computer.  In another corner is a Dejarik table.  Han installed
smuggling compartments in the floor.  A few chairs are scattered around the
room. This is a cargo ship and not a passenger liner so comfort isn't in
abundance.

ExtraDescs.Description: Under the movable floorboards are large holes, used for smuggling.

Dejarik is a game similar to chess.  The board is round and the pieces are
generated holographically.

rooms.Name: Cockpit of the Millenium Falcon
rooms.Description:
This is a rather small compartment.  The back three walls are covered with
buttons, switches, dials, and flashing lights.  In front of you are the main
controls that fly this ship.  Through the canopy, the stars appear as white
streaks because you are traveling at .5 past light speed.  There are four
captain's chairs so you can sit back and enjoy the ride.

rooms.Name: Inside the Millenium Falcon
rooms.Description:
You are standing in the center of the crew quarters.  One wall is occupied 
by the navi-computer.  In another corner is a Dejarik table.  Han installed
smuggling compartments in the floor.  A few chairs are scattered around the
room. This is a cargo ship and not a passenger liner so comfort isn't in
abundance.

ExtraDescs.Description:
Dejarik is similar to chess.  The board is round and the pieces are generated
holographically.
Under the movable floorboards are large holes, used for smuggling.

rooms.Name: Cockpit of the Millenium Falcon
rooms.Description:
This is a rather small compartment.  The back three walls are covered with
buttons, switches, dials, and flashing lights.  In front of you are the main
controls that fly this ship.  Through the canopy, the stars appear as white
streaks because you are traveling at .5 past light speed.  There are four
captain's chairs so you can sit back and enjoy the ride.

rooms.Name: Entrance Ramp of the Millenium Falcon
rooms.Description:
You have just stepped onto the ramp leading into the Millenium Falcon.  The
guy who brought you here is nowhere to be found.  Hope that the old man got
the tractor beam out of comission and pray you can fly this bucket of bolts.

rooms.Name: Control room of the S.O.L.
rooms.Description:
You are standing in the control room of the Satellite of Love.  It looks
like the walls have been decorated with household garbage then spray
painted with gray primer.  Then there's that corny blue mood lighting.  On
the west wall is a Hex-field viewscreen, on which a nuclear bomb is whining
about not being needed.  In the east wall is a porthole that looks into the
vastness of space.  The opening to the Umbilicon is in the floor, and a large
set of double doors is south.  In the center of the room is a long
countertop with three warning lights in the center.  The lights begin to
flash....Oh No, It's Movie Sign!

Exits.Description: It's a door, so it looks like a door.
The opening leads to a dark tube.

rooms.Name: Hall of doors
rooms.Description:
On a regular basis as you walk down the hall, a door slides, swings, falls
open in front of you.  It seems like you are walking from one end of the
satellite to the other.  It also feels like you are in some kind of countdown.
The decor of this hallway leaves something to be desired, being the same as
is the control room.  A cockroach barely avoids the underside of your shoe as
it scurries across the floor.

Exits.Description: The hatch looks like a round, heavy safe door, complete with a wheel latch.

ExtraDescs.Description:
Ack, the roach looks like every other roach you've ever seen; brown, six legs,
long antennae. This one has an attitude, almost daring you to step on it.

rooms.Name: Theatre
rooms.Description:
This room, like every other theatre, is completely dark.  The only lights come
the door which you just entered and from the projector, so it is almost
impossible to make out the details of this room.  You can see that there is
only one row of seats.  Some silly 'B' rated Sci-Fi movie is playingso sit
down and make a few cracks about it.

Exits.Description: It's dark...
A long time ago, in a galaxy far, far away...

ExtraDescs.Description: A long time ago in a galaxy far, far away...

rooms.Name: In the Umbili-con
rooms.Description:
The Umbili-con is a scientific breakthrough, making the Satellite of Love the
first tethered object in orbit.  You can't believe that you actually squeezed
yourself into this tube, the Umbili-con just isn't wide enough to fit people.
It is a thirty-mile long, one-foot diameter, corrugated, black pipe.  You
feel yourself getting heavier, so you must be getting closer to the surface.
Remember to hold your breath, because space is a vacuum...

rooms.Name: Deep 13
rooms.Description:
Deep 13 is the lab where Dr. Forrester runs the experiment on Mike and the
Bots.  Deep 13 is aptly named, this room was carved out of the rock thirteen
stories below the surface by the Gizmonic Institute.  The room's lack of
light gives off an eerie feeling of Hell.  One corner of the room is filled
with cheesy movies, the worst we can find.  On one of the walls
is a large viewscreen so that Deep 13 is always in contact with the S.o.L.
Ahhhh, push the button Frank.
